         <h1> ANDROMEDA GALAXY </h1>
         <p> The Andromeda Galaxy, also known as Messier 31, M31, or NGC 224 and originally the Andromeda Nebula, is a barred spiral galaxy approximately 2.5 million light-years from Earth and the nearest large galaxy to the Milky Way</p>
         <br>
         <h1> THE BLUE MARBLE </h1>
         <p> The Blue Marble is an image of Earth taken on December 7, 1972, . It was taken by the crew of the Apollo 17 spacecraft on its way to the Moon, and is one of the most reproduced images in history.
         NOTE : First Image Of The Earth From Somewhere In Space...</p>
